{"lemma":"شَفْرِ","slug":"شَفْرِ","root":"ش.ف.ر","root_slug":"ش-ف-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ف-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22618","n22619","n22620","n22621","n22622"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"edge of anything"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"labium"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to encode, to encrypt, to encipher"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Denominal verb of شِيفْرَة (šīfra, “cipher”), from French chiffre or Italian cifra, themselves ultimately from Arabic صِفْر (ṣifr, “zero”)."},"ipa":["/ʃafr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22618","headword_ar":"شَفْرٌ","root":"$fr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph, in four places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n22619","headword_ar":"شُفْرٌ","root":"$fr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of growth of the eyelash,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, T, S, A, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is the edge of the eyelid;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aforN","text_ar":"شَفْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr, A, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afiyrN","text_ar":"شَفِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or, accord. to some, this last signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper side of the inner angle of the eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and with the vulgar, the first signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eyelash;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this is [said to be] a mistake: (IKt, Msb:) it occurs, however, in this sense, in a trad. of Esh-Shaabee; (IAth, TA;) and in like manner the pl. occurs in another trad.; but the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEar","text_ar":"شَعَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"should be considered as understood before it; or what grows is thus called by the name of the places of growth, and the like of this is not rare: (Mgh:) it is of the masc. gender: (Lh, K:) and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ofaArN","text_ar":"اَشْفَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, S, Mgh, Msb,) the only pl. form. (Sb, TA.) [Hence,] one says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA biAld~aAri $aforN","text_ar":"مَا بِالدَّارِ شَفْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ks, Fr, T, S, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uforN","text_ar":"شُفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, Msb, K,) but Sh disallows this latter, (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aforapN","text_ar":"شَفْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, Sgh, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not in the house any one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, &c.:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA raA^ayotu","text_ar":"مَا رَاَيْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minohumo $aforFA","text_ar":"مِنْهُمْ شَفْرًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw not of them any one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$fr","text_ar":"شفر"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the eye: meaning one having a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$fr","text_ar":"شفر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$fr","text_ar":"شفر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used in this sense without a negation. (TA.) One says likewise,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA tarakati Als~anapu","text_ar":"مَا تَرَكَتِ السَّنَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZuforFA walaA $uforFA","text_ar":"ظُفْرًا وَلَا شُفْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The year of drought left not anything:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes they said ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aforFA","text_ar":"شَفْرًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h, and in this case they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaforFA","text_ar":"ظَفْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", for assimilation. (A.) ―         -b2-  Also, (S A, Mgh, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afiyrN","text_ar":"شَفِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"edge, border, margin, brink, brow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K,) of anything; (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K;) as of a valley and the like, (S,) or as of a river &c.: (Mgh and Msb, in relation to the latter word:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~ahori","text_ar":"النَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEaduwA EalaY $afiyri","text_ar":"قَعَدُوا عَلَى شَفِيرِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albiy^ori","text_ar":"البِيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqabori","text_ar":"القَبْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They sat upon the side of the river,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the well,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the grave:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) and both words signify the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side of the upper part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a valley. (K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~uforu","text_ar":"الشُّفْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uforu Alfaroji","text_ar":"شُفْرُ الفَرْجِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uforu AlmaroA^api","text_ar":"شُفْرُ المَرْاَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The edge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"border,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the vulva,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"external portion of the organs of generation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of each of the labia majora,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a woman:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ofaArN","text_ar":"اَشْفَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isokataAni","text_ar":"اـِسْكَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are the two sides [or labia majora] of the vulva of a woman; and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uforaAni","text_ar":"شُفْرَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two borders of the said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsktAn","text_ar":"اسكتان"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AHeyth, Mgh, TA:) Lth says that the ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAfiraAni","text_ar":"شَافِرَانِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"are ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two parts"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the pudendum muliebre:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uforu Alr~aHimi","text_ar":"شُفْرُ الرَّحِمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAfiruhaA","text_ar":"شَافِرُهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify [in like manner]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the edges of the vulva:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uforaA AlmaroA^api","text_ar":"شُفْرَا المَرْاَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAfiraAhaA","text_ar":"شَافِرَاهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two edges of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHim","text_ar":"رَحِم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vulva"},{"kind":"text","text":"(for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aHim","text_ar":"الرَّحِم"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here used tropically, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfaroj","text_ar":"الفَرْج"},{"kind":"text","text":", as it is in many other instances,)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a woman."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Sh","T","S","A","Msb","K","Kr","TA","IKt","Mgh","Lh","Sb","Ks","Fr","Sgh","AHeyth"]},{"entry_id":"n22620","headword_ar":"شِفْرٌ","root":"$fr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aforapN","text_ar":"شَفْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n22621","headword_ar":"شَفَرٌ","root":"$fr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safanN","text_ar":"سَفَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n22622","headword_ar":"شَفِرٌ","root":"$fr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[an epithet of which the fem. only is mentioned]."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afirapN","text_ar":"شَفِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afiyrapN","text_ar":"شَفِيرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify A woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who experiences the gratification of her venereal lust"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahowatahaA","text_ar":"شَهْوَتَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in her"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ufor","text_ar":"شُفْر"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that she emits"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tunozilu","text_ar":"تُنْزِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"speedily:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or [in the CK “ and ”]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is content with the least of coitus:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEirapN","text_ar":"قَعِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEiyrapN","text_ar":"قَعِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}